        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 9:13PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 913 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near French Corner, or 9 miles north of Emmett, moving
northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust reducing
visibility. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Ola around 930 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
